{
  "stem": "24346.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We found out that there was a camp 40 kilometers away, there's a camp with Jewish girls, only women, from the Lodz ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we got some bicycles, a few guys-- [NON-ENGLISH], a few guys-- and we went to look for these Jewish girls, to Salzwedel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We traveled by foot, hills, up-- it was a hard job.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we came there, we arrived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I asked people, where are people from the Lodz ghetto?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they point in this building.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went in there and I found neighbors.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We used to live, before they dispossessed us-- where I told you after I got the job.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We used to live [NON-ENGLISH], 2, number 2.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They moved me as superintendent to [NON-ENGLISH] 20, a few hours away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, at [NON-ENGLISH] 4, the next building to ours, used to be-- the guy used to make taps from shoes, a manufacturer.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his son and his daughter, they knew me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had the deli right next to their store, or only two stores away, and they knew me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said, you-- did you see my mother?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when they evacuated the ghetto to Auschwitz, they took houses, areas.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And these two went on the same train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this is the one that told me, your mother went to the wrong side where they didn't go to the camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there, I found that my mother perished in Auschwitz after they liquidated the Lodz ghetto, in September.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was about six months after they took me away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They liquidated the total ghetto, because the Russians were approaching there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So from-- from that woman, I found that my mother was killed, somehow in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
